{
  "text": "An example of ASPP, which consists of one 1 × 1 convolution, and three 3×3 convolutions with atrous rates being equal to [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , is given in Fig. 4 . The four different atrous convolution branches (corresponding to 4 different atrous rates) have the same input and their outputs are combined. The final output can be viewed as the sampling of all feature maps from the four branches with different scales of receptive fields. Therefore, ASPP is able to robustly segment objects at multiple scales effectively.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "207763512",
